&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description: Staffing Execution Lead – India (Global Advisory)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: India&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reports to: Head of Staffing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Scope: Ignite Advisory (global coordination; India talent pool)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Inizio&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inizio is a global partner with over 10,500 experts across more than 50 countries, supporting health and life sciences companies in turning science into strategy and execution across the product and patient journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Inizio Ignite&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inizio Ignite is the global advisory partner for health and life sciences, bringing together Research Partnership, Putnam, Vynamic, and STEM to deliver strategy, insights, and transformation that create lasting impact for patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Staffing Execution Lead – India plays a critical dual role:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Driving day-to-day staffing execution across all Ignite Advisory businesses using the India-based consultant pool, and&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building and evolving the staffing infrastructure, processes, and operating model to support a rapidly scaling global delivery hub.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This role serves as the central coordination point for India-based talent deployment, partnering closely with global Staffing Leads, business leadership, and cross-functional stakeholders to balance client demand, consultant development, and utilization goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a net-new and high-impact role, this individual will bring a builder mindset, helping define scalable staffing processes, systems, and governance while ensuring alignment with global staffing practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staffing Execution &amp;amp; Talent Deployment (Core Priority)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-to-end staffing for India-based consultants across Ignite Advisory, aligning talent to project demand.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with global Staffing Leads and business leadership to balance demand, resolve staffing needs, and optimize utilization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary liaison between India talent supply and global demand, ensuring visibility into skills, availability, and development goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead staffing discussions with consultants to understand preferences, skills, and career aspirations, enabling informed placements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively manage capacity, pipeline risks, and staffing conflicts; escalate issues and recommend solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and continuously improve unstaffed and new hire staffing processes, ensuring strong onboarding and deployment experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate and up-to-date skills, experience, and availability data within staffing systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Global Coordination &amp;amp; Stakeholder Management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with US/UK Staffing Leads to enable seamless global staffing and cross-region resourcing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with India-based business leaders to validate demand, improve visibility of talent capabilities, and enhance decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with BD, finance, and opportunity leads to ensure pipeline accuracy and staffing alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a trusted advisor to leadership on staffing insights, risks, and trade-offs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive consistency, transparency, and best practice sharing across staffing teams globally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staffing Infrastructure Build &amp;amp; Process Design (Critical Focus)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define, build, and implement the India staffing operati

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Accountant&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Data Accountant is a 12 month fixed term contract role within the Record-to-Report (RTR) function of Global Finance Services (GFS). The role is based in Manchester.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will sit within the RTR function of GFS and is responsible for the integrity, quality and continuous improvement of financial data and controls across the GFS operating model. It is analytical and controls-focused. Combining hands-on finance operations knowledge with ownership of the GFS actuals reporting infrastructure, it also has a forward-looking responsibility. This responsibility is to embed AI tools and data-driven working practices into GFS processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a finance professional with RTR knowledge, a practical understanding of financial controls, and the technical capability to design and own a self-service reporting suite. You will bring hands-on experience of period-end close, SOX compliance and data analysis, combined with fluency in Power BI and AI tools. You will be comfortable operating across multiple entities and communicating findings to a CFO-facing audience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Controls and RTR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete and report on SOX journal testing (RTR-2.6.1), document results and lead remediation of issues identified.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help maintain the GFS controls framework, including the CSA programme and control self-assessments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor reconciliation completion and quality during month-end and report final status to GFS leadership; work in collaboration with Intelligent Enterprises to ensure ARCS master data is accurate and reconciliation automation is optimised.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and escalate data integrity issues, including those originating in supplier or customer master data, that affect financial reporting accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support internal and external audit with clean, well-documented data extracts and process evidence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Variance Reporting and Analytics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A core output of this role is the develop and ongoing ownership of the GFS actuals variance reporting suite. This covers monthly and quarterly cycles across the P&amp;amp;L and Balance Sheet, and GFS accountants refresh and operate it independently. Forecast and budget variance analysis sits with FP&amp;amp;A and is outside the scope of this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop monthly P&amp;amp;L reporting packs covering month-on-month actuals movements by cost centre and GFS process tower (RTR, PTP, OTC), with exception commentary frameworks to support accountant review.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop monthly Balance Sheet packs covering month-on-month movements by entity, with ageing analysis and reconciliation status where relevant.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop quarterly packs covering quarter-on-quarter and year-on-year P&amp;amp;L and Balance Sheet movements, with trend analysis and narrative support for GFS leadership reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build all reports to be self-refreshing or one-click refreshable by GFS accountants using Power BI, Power Query or equivalent, with no dependency on manual data manipulation by the Data Accountant.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce clear data dictionaries and refresh guides so accountants can operate, interpret and present packs without technical support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the underlying data model: ensure source data connections from Oracle Fusion a

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employee Relations Administrator&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Employee Relations Administrator, you will support a variety of administrative tasks relating to the Employee Relations business at Inizio. This includes locating and organising SharePoint files, creating standardised templates and letters, transfer of information from support systems such as ServiceNow and Navex, and creating draft communications from meeting notes. This role may also provide additional support in processing Excel data for various areas of the business and creating PowerPoint presentations to provide this data to senior-level leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will report to our Global Employee Relations Lead and will work on a hybrid basis, working partly remotely and partly from our office in Gurugram. Your working hours will be from 1-10pm to align to the UK/Ireland and South Africa and allow crossover with East Coast US timezones.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will be doing&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with a SharePoint system to organise current Employee Relations files and documents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with a SharePoint system to locate documents related to Employee Relations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with Service Now and Navex to create cases and ensure files and case notes are kept up to date and accurate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with documents from a variety of countries to create consistent and harmonised templates and letters that can be used by Employee Relations, managers, and the People team to support in employee related processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creating letters and scripts for the Employee Relations Specialists and Global Employee Relations Lead&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with Service Now and Navex to run reports and correlate the data for senior-level management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creating slide decks for review to be used with senior-level management and the People team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reviewing and amending MS teams transcripts and/or taking meeting notes for the Employee Relations Specialists and Global Employee Relations Lead&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting with wider People Services administrative tasks as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will bring to the role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Organisational Skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Communication and Interpersonal Skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in SharePoint or similar systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in database collection systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with Microsoft Office applications – Word, Excel, PowerPoint etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience drafting ER case letters, scripts, templates, and processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General understanding of labour laws and regulations as they relate to the UK and Ireland, US, and South Africa is desirable, but not essential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We help our clients navigate their clinical development and commercialisation journey by connecting the best scientific knowledge, market intelligence, actionable data, technology, communication, and creative execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With a global presence and multiple career paths, the career possibilities are expanding at Inizio. We’re a growing global team of 11,700 - a $1.5bn revenue business working with the world’s leading health and life sciences businesses, and we have exciting growth plans. Whoever and wherever you are, we’ll empower you with the autonomy you need to experiment, learn, and grow. We’ll make sure that you feel valued, supported and, of course, because we’re helping our clients to transform healthcare and improve millions of lives you can feel pride in your work at Inizio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employee Relations Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Employee Relations (ER) Specialist supports INIZIO&#39;s processes, policies, and strategy across ER. You will act as a liaison between legal and business matters. In this role, you will act as a risk mitigation arm of HR, supporting ER policy creation. Additionally, you will drive consistency across case outcomes and provide a system-wide approach and guidance. You will partner with important stakeholders to enhance employee experience with system-wide ER practices and to define the ER scope of services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will report to the Global Employee Relations Lead. This is a remote-working role (you are welcome to work from one of our office locations). Time zones are flexible, so long as business needs are met.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the ER strategy and approach at a global, organization-wide level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the ER business process needed to run an equitable and clear ER process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with HR Partners to develop strategies to respond to team member concerns and infuse ER into broader company practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support employee relations best practices and strategies for managing supervisor problems and employee grievances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with HR and business leaders to identify and address potential employee relations issues and develop preventive measures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist managers and supervisors in understanding and implementing procedures for managing their employees.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with regulations and comply with reporting requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support administrative departments regarding inputting data, creating letters, scripts, transcribing meeting notes, creating PowerPoint presentations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support meeting with management to better understand needs and concerns relating to requests they have submitted to the Employee Relations team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct investigations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support performance improvement processes and review performance improvement documents provided by management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you bring to the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 years of experience supporting employee relations functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-depth knowledge of human resources and employee relations principles, practices, and procedures in the US and UK .&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using data to guide decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with performance management and employee relations processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience promoting a vision and translating it into an executable strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evidence of leading at a strategic level .&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to handle confidential information with utmost discretion and professionalism.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong case management and project management skills, with the ability to manage multiple priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Package and Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;20 days PTO + 10 personal/sick days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company bonus plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous retirement plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive Medical, Dental, and Optical cover&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HSA (Health Savings Account)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About iNIZIO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Inizio, we&#39;re a global team driven by a shared purpose: to reimagine health. Formed in 2022 through the coming together of Ashfield and Huntsworth, we unite decades of experience with cutting-edge capabilities to deliver impactful solutions across the commercializati

&lt;p&gt;You will support our Chief People Officer, being a trusted partner to allow them to operate at pace and with maximum impact. As a member of the Executive Leadership Team, the CPO operates at the heart of the organisation, and you will provide critical support in navigating that environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will sit at the centre of the People function, where you will also provide administrative and coordination support to the broader HR leadership team. You will work with other Executive Assistants and senior partners across the business to ensure understanding, seamless coordination, and communication at the executive level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll ensure the smooth running of daily activities, while also contributing to the organisation and delivery of important People initiatives. This includes managing complex scheduling, preparing high-quality presentations and materials, coordinating leadership meetings, and supporting the planning and delivery of internal events.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hybrid-working role reporting to the Chief People Officer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage priorities and time, providing proactive, daily support to the Chief People Officer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage complex scheduling across multiple time zones, including meetings, travel, and important People and Executive Leadership forums&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with Executive Assistants in the wider Executive Leadership Team to ensure agreement of priorities, meetings, and communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the wider HR leadership team where required with administrative coordination, diary management, and meeting logistics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare high-quality presentations, reports, and briefing materials for executive and board-level discussions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate board and management packs, ensuring accuracy and proactive delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the planning and delivery of internal events, offsite events, and leadership sessions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the central point of coordination across HR, tracking progress, managing deadlines, and following up on actions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor project status and produce clear reporting for leadership visibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with other teams and external partners to support operational processes, including vendor management and payments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the contact for senior team members, both internally and externally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify potential risks, bottlenecks, or delays and work with team members to resolve them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record as a successful Executive Assistant in a global organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A motivated team player who can rise to any challenge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practice strict confidentiality with all materials, and exercises discretion when working with the business – familiarity with confidential HR matters is a bonus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Microsoft Office with aptitude to learn new software and systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a comprehensive benefits package designed to support your health, financial wellbeing and work-life balance, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company bonus plan&lt;/strong&gt; predicated on company and individual performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Private Healthcare Allowance&lt;/strong&gt; with access to corporate healthcare plans through VHI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Inizio&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Inizio, we&#39;re a global team driven by a shared purpose: to reimagine health. Formed in 2022 through the coming together of Ashfield and Huntsworth, we unite decades of experience with cutting-edge capabilities to deliver impactful solutions across the commercialization journey - from discovery to post-launch. Our global network of over 10,000 experts operates across 50 countries, supporting clients with strategic insight, medical excellence, creative engagement, and real-world delivery. We work with the world&#39;s leading health and life sciences businesses to solve complex challenges and drive meaningful outcomes for our clients and patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What sets Inizio apart is our people - and we believe everyone should have the opportunity to thrive. Here, you&#39;re encouraged to reimagine your possibilities: to grow, to be curious and to make real change happen. It&#39;s a place where your individuality is valued, your development is supported, and your ambition is celebrated. If you&#39;re ready to push boundaries and accelerate your career, Inizio is the best place to be.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Global Benefits Director to lead the design, implementation, and ongoing management of our benefits programs, with a strong focus on the U.S. and key markets including the UK and Ireland.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires a thoughtful, planful, and commercially minded leader who is both strategic and hands-on — a strong project and stakeholder manager who can build and execute a cohesive benefits strategy while driving cost discipline and operational rigor. This individual will be entrepreneurial and proactive, able to operate at pace, take ownership, and drive both strategy and execution in a fast-moving environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role partners closely with HR, Finance, and senior leadership to ensure benefits programs are aligned with business objectives, cost targets, and talent strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
