&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Group Accounting Manager &lt;/strong&gt;will play a key role within the Group Finance function, support internal and external reporting under IFRS and to provide technical accounting leadership to the wider group finance and senior leadership teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Head of Group Accounting and working closely with, FP&amp;amp;A, Tax and Treasury, and external advisors, the successful candidate will provide technical accounting guidance across the business, support a range of Group finance and technical accounting projects, and contribute to the delivery of the Group&#39;s external financial reporting and Annual Report process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is based in Dublin, Ireland. You must be willing to come into the office at least three days/week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Preparation of group annual reports under IFRS.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Preparation of monthly consolidated group management information.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Provide technical accounting and regulatory guidance (IFRS) to internal customers and stakeholders on key accounting issues impacting the business.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Perform a key role in assessing the impact of any new accounting standards/regulatory changes and related implementation.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proficient in operating in and leading a strong SOX control environment and providing guidance and direction to the wider group finance team for continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal customers and stakeholders to develop &amp;amp; continually improve processes &amp;amp; systems for both external and internal financial reporting.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with interdisciplinary teams to develop and implement group strategy and projects (legal, tax, treasury, IT, finance).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Support the preparation of statutory financial statements and the related audit process.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Coach and mentor junior members of the group accounting team.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;
