&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Research Manager will play a pivotal role in the new hub, reporting to an Associate Director.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll be doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your role will involve supporting the day-to-day delivery of multiple quantitative research projects, ensuring timelines are met and outputs are delivered to a high standard.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will write and refine questionnaires, with input from senior team members, ensuring alignment with research objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will be responsible for conducting analysis, including reviewing data tables, coding open-end responses and supporting development of table specifications, ensuring outputs are accurate and robust.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will contribute to the preparation of client deliverables, including drafting report templates in PowerPoint and supporting the development of final reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will work closely with project management teams to support fieldwork execution and troubleshoot any issues that arise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will provide regular updates to your manager on project progress and will begin to contribute to internal discussions on findings and implications.&lt;/li&gt;
